column8: Notes
Female shot first (active)
gives verbal commands, doesnt shoot until S w/ knife lunges
Not much info, Agency Assist w/ Mesa PD
Female used taser instead of gun (assist/passive)
Guns were drawn but both female officers were behind male officer
Male officer was killed and both females injured
attempts to deescalate for extended period - then fires only one shot
extended period of de-escalation before shooting - 2 shots fired.
active - shoots at the same time as male officer
Shoots after two rounds of taser.
shoots at the same time as male.

Shoots at the same time as males. One is a sergeant, others are officers. Not sure which one the female officer is, but assuming she is an officer.  Female officer tried to de-escalate by talking to the man.
Female is addressing the girlfriend (who has a suicidal boyfriend) and  is shot. Then the male officer takes cover and shoots back.
Sergeant
Large incident with multiple officers involved - including females
female doesn't turn on body cam during shots fired but is part of the initial shots
Video from 11/29 duplicated here.
Detective and officer
Other two officers used tasers.
Sergeant and two officers.
Other male assisted but did not shoot.
Other male assisted but did not shoot.
Another male officer was present and almost shot, but did not.
Sergeant and Officer both shot at the suspect, many male officers assissted.
Other male officers assisted, one used a taser.
One other male officer was involved and used a pepperball launcher as a form of less lethal
Other officer on scene used a taser to assist the Sergeant who shot the suspect.
Video footage is no longer available - cannot tell the gender of the second officer involved,
Female officer assisted by firing less lethal 44mm and helped with the arrest of the suspect afterwards.
Both officers shot at suspect.
The shooting occurred right as the officers were pulling up to the suspects. Officer in passenger seat is the one who shot the suspect.
BWCs of officers shooting at the suspect were damaged, so the footage comes from a witnessing officer. It seems like all officers present were male, but uncertain.

Female officer originally tried to arrest and detain the suspect during a stop, but the suspect broke free (with a gun in his waistband) and ran off. Female officer called for assistance, and multiuple male officers and a helicopter came to her aid. One male officer shot the suspect, while the other officers (including the female officer) assisted/were backup.
Officer who actually shot has 6 years of service. The female officer was the one furthest behind, telling civilians to get out of the way, and told the suspect to drop their knife from a distance.
Tactical Support Bureau/FAID - lots of officers on scene. All men from what I can see.
Lieutenant
